@NODE FORMATS "Formats"
@{b}@{u}3.1 Formats@{uu}@{ub}

@{b}Load :@{ub} 

@{u}IFF ILBM@{uu}

Amigaź standard format, up to 256 color format supported compressed or
uncompressed (ByteRun1 / XPK). No 24 bit pictures yet.

@{u}Datatypes@{uu}

All installed and to the system known picture Datatypes are supported.

@{u}IFF XTVF@{uu}

XTrace format (@{b}XT@{ub}race @{b}V@{ub}ector @{b}F@{ub}ormat) Is used to save all important
data (all bitmap and/or vektor data) of a picture.

@{b}Save :@{ub} 

@{u}IFF XTVF@{uu}

XTrace format (see above)

@{b}Export :@{ub} 

@{u}IFF DR2D@{uu}

Very compact IFF vector format, used by PageStream, ProVector etc. Very useful
for Amigaź-only applications (PageStream, Provector, DrawStudio ...).

@{u}EPSF@{uu}

System independant vector format by Adobeź, Inc. Copyright by Adobeź, Inc.

Is supported by nearly all DTP-programs and others, as well as UNIX, Mac-OS,
Amiga OS, MS-DOS and Windows.

Needs lot of memory, but high compress factor.

@{u}EPSI@{uu}

System independant vector format by Adobeź, Inc. Copyright by Adobeź, Inc.

Like EPSF, but includes a preview picture in ASCII-format.

@{u}EPSB@{uu}

System independant vector format by Adobeź, Inc. Copyright by Adobeź, Inc.

Like EPSF, but includes a preview picture in TIFF-format.

The preview picture will be saved with a transparency mask, to display
transparent areas, created by @{"Make pen transparent" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_MAKEPENTRANS }, also in the preview
transparent. Unfortunately, some programs doesn't support this feature of TIFF
V6.0.

@{u}Adobe Illustratorź@{uu}

System independant vector format by Adobeź, Inc. Copyright by Adobeź, Inc.

Is supported by many DTP-programs and others, as well as UNIX, Mac-OS, Amiga OS,
MS-DOS and Windows.

Needs lot of memory, but high compress factor.

This format is a extension to the orginal EPS format, expanded with some 
capabilities.

@{u}FIG@{uu}

System independant vector format, which can be read for example by FIG programs,
which exists on several systems (e.g. Amiga: xFig, AmiFIG; UNIX: xFig; ...)

Copyright by Supoj Sutanthavibul, Brian V. Smith, Paul King

@{u}Navigator Titler Logo@{uu}

3D-Format for Michiel den Outer's Navigator Titler (Aminet) (see @{"FAQ" link FAQ} also).

@{u}DXF 2D@{uu}

System independant vector format by Autodesk, Inc. Copyright by Autodesk, Inc.

With this format, you can import vectorpictures from XTrace into CAD programs.

@{u}DXF 3D@{uu}

System independant vector format by Autodesk, Inc. Copyright by Autodesk, Inc.

With this format, you can import vectorpictures from XTrace as 3-dimensional
object into, for example, raytracers.

@{u}HP-GL@{uu}

System independant vector format by Hewlett-Packard Company. Copyright by
Hewlett-Packard Company.

Vectorformat orginally designed to control plotters. Can also be used with
PCL printers which most support also HP-GL/2.

@{u}Navigator Titler Font@{uu}

3D-Font-Format for Michiel den Outer's Navigator Titler (Aminet) (see @{"FAQ" link FAQ} also).

@{u}IFF ILBM@{uu}

See above, usage of XTrace bitmap operators.
@ENDNODE

@NODE FAQ "Frequently Asked Questions"
@{b}@{u}3.2 Frequently Asked Questions@{uu}@{ub}

 @{b}Q:@{ub} How can I create 3D fonts for NTitler ?

 @{b}A:@{ub} 1. Load the font with the menue item @{"Project / Load font" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_LOADFONT}.

    2. Trace it with @{"Bitmap process / Trace" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_TRACE}

    3. Use the @{"Slope" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_SLOPE} operator if you want to remove jaggy borders of
       the traced image.

    4. Export it with @{"Project / Export picture / Vectors" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_EXPORTPIC}
       as "Navigator Titler Font". With "Settings" in this window you can 
       specify further values for the font.

 @{b}Q:@{ub} How can I create 3D logos for NTitler ?

 @{b}A:@{ub} 1. Load the picture with the menue item @{"Project / Load logo" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_LOADPIC}.

    2. Trace it with @{"Bitmap process / Trace" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_TRACE}, if it not yet
       traced.
   
    3. Use the @{"Slope" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_SLOPE} operator if you want to remove jaggy borders of
       the chars.

    4. Export it with @{"Project / Export picture / Vectors" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_EXPORTPIC}
       as "Navigator Titler Logo". With "Settings" in this window you can 
       specify further values for the logo.

 @{b}Q:@{ub} How can I create 3D DXF files for, for example, the raytracer ?

 @{b}A:@{ub} 1. - 3. See previous question.

    4. Export it with @{"Project / Export picture / Vectors" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_EXPORTPIC}
       as "DXF 3D". With "Settings" in this window you can specify further
       values for the object.
@ENDNODE
